article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- — Dyondre Dominguez scored 26 points as Arkansas State beat Georgia Southern 109-83 on Thursday night. Dominguez had 12 rebounds for the Red Wolves (5-9, 1-1 Sun Belt Conference). Taryn Todd scored 20 points while going 8 of 12 (2 for 4 from 3-point range), and added eight assists. Derrian Ford shot 4 for 9 (3 for 5 from 3-point range) and 4 of 4 from the free-throw line to finish with 15 points. The Eagles (1-13, 1-1) were led in scoring by Eren Banks, who finished with 15 points. Jamar Franklin added 13 points and two steals for Georgia Southern. In addition, Nate Brafford finished with 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
